workflow.name: Automate AI-powered quiz generation from PDFs with Google Forms
workflow.description:
## ‚úÖ What problem does this workflow solve?

Teachers, coaches, and educators spend **hours manually creating quizzes** from study notes and PDFs. This workflow eliminates that effort by using **AI to convert PDF study material into fully functional quizzes**, complete with scoring, student tracking, and Google Form integration ‚Äî all automatically.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è What does this workflow do?

- Accepts study material as a **PDF upload**
- Extracts educational content from the document
- Uses AI to generate **high-quality MCQ questions**
- Automatically creates a **Google Quiz Form**
- Saves all questions and correct answers for teacher reference
- Enables **instant scoring and response tracking** for students

---

## üß† How It Works ‚Äì Step-by-Step

### 1. üìÑ Upload Study Material (PDF)
- Teachers upload a PDF via an **n8n Form Trigger**
- They specify how many quiz questions they want

### 2. üìö PDF Parsing & AI Question Generation
- The workflow extracts text from the PDF
- An **AI Teacher Agent** powered by :contentReference[oaicite:1]{index=1}:
  - Identifies key learning concepts
  - Generates **multiple-choice questions**
  - Ensures:
    - 4 options per question
    - One correct answer
    - Clear and student-friendly language

### 3. üìù Quiz Creation (Google Forms)
- A new **Google Form** is created automatically
- Quiz mode is enabled with:
  - Point values
  - Correct/incorrect feedback
  - Option shuffling
- Student detail fields (Name, Email, ID, Class) are added

### 4. üìä Teacher Reference & Record Keeping
- All generated questions are logged in **Google Sheets**
- Stored data includes:
  - Question text
  - All options
  - Correct answers
  - Quiz URL

### 5. üéì Student Submission & Scoring
- Students take the quiz via Google Forms
- Scores are calculated automatically
- Teachers receive all responses in the connected Google Sheet

---

## üõ† Tools & Integrations Used

- **n8n Form Trigger** ‚Äì File upload & inputs
- **PDF Parser** ‚Äì Extracts text from documents
- **OpenAI Chat Model** ‚Äì AI question generation
- **Google Forms API** ‚Äì Quiz creation & scoring
- **Google Sheets** ‚Äì Question storage & response tracking

---

## üí° Key Benefits

- ‚è± Saves hours of manual quiz creation
- üìö Ensures pedagogically sound questions
- üìä Automatic grading & analytics
- üß† Consistent difficulty & coverage
- üîÅ Easily reusable for different subjects

---

## üë§ Who can use this?

Perfect for:
- üßë‚Äçüè´ **Teachers & Professors**
- üè´ **Coaching centers**
- üéì **EdTech & LMS platforms**
- üöÄ **SaaS founders building quiz tools**

If you want to transform static PDFs into **interactive, AI-generated assessments**, this workflow is built for you.

parameters.content:
## How it works

This workflow automatically generates Google Forms quizzes from PDF documents using AI. Upload a PDF and specify the number of questions‚Äîthe AI extracts content, creates multiple-choice questions with correct answers, builds a Google Form with student information fields, and logs all questions to a Google Sheet for record-keeping.

## Setup steps

1. **Connect credentials**: Add Google OAuth2 API credentials for form creation and Google Sheets OAuth2 for data logging
2. **Add OpenAI API**: Configure OpenAI credentials for the AI model
3. **Configure Google Sheet**: Update the sheet ID in "Append All Questions" node to your target spreadsheet
4. **Test the form**: Submit a PDF through the form trigger URL to generate your first quiz

## Input Section
Form trigger accepts PDF uploads and question count from users

## AI Processing Section
Extracts PDF text and uses OpenAI to generate structured quiz questions with answers

## Form Creation Section
Builds Google Form with quiz mode, adds AI-generated questions and student info fields

## Output Section
Formats and logs all questions with answers to Google Sheets for tracking
